BoostHub.sol
Harvest Not Called Before Withdraw - Stakers Lose Uncollected Rewards
The `withdraw` function does not call `_harvest` before `_checkpoint`. When a strategy withdraws, `_checkpoint` is called to finalize pending rewards based on the current `accRewardPerShare`. However, if there are uncollected rewards sitting in the gauge that haven't been harvested yet, `accRewardPerShare` is stale and the withdrawing strategy will not receive credit for rewards earned up to the point of withdrawal. After the withdrawal reduces `pool.totalStaked`, any subsequent harvest will distribute those uncollected rewards over a smaller staked base, effectively giving the remaining stakers a larger share of rewards that the withdrawing strategy was entitled to.


