BoostHub.sol
Fee-on-Transfer Token Accounting Discrepancy in _harvest
The `_harvest` function snapshots token balances before calling `claim_rewards`, then computes `harvested = IERC20(tokens[i]).balanceOf(address(this)) - beforeBalances[i]`. This correctly accounts for the actual received amount. However, when `_chargeFees` is called and transfers fees to recipients, if the reward token is a fee-on-transfer token, the actual amount received by the fee recipient will be less than `platformFee` or `reserveFee`. The `net` calculation `amount - platformFee - reserveFee` will be correct in terms of what was deducted from the contract's perspective, but the fee recipients will receive less than expected. More critically, when the net amount is added to `accRewardPerShare`, it represents the correct amount held by the contract, so staker accounting remains correct. The issue is primarily that fee recipients receive less than the configured fee amount.


