BoostHub.sol
DoS: Malicious or Broken Gauge Can Block All Deposits via _harvest Revert
The `deposit` function calls `_harvest` internally before processing the deposit. `_harvest` calls `IStakeDaoGauge(pool.gauge).claim_rewards(address(this), address(this))` as an external call. If the gauge's `claim_rewards` function reverts for any reason (e.g., gauge is paused, gauge is broken, gauge has a bug, or a malicious gauge is configured), the entire `deposit` transaction will revert. This creates a DoS condition where no new deposits can be made to the pool. Similarly, the public `harvest` function is also blocked. While the owner can set the pool to inactive, this doesn't help existing stakers who need to deposit more.


