BoostHub.sol
Reward Distribution Skipped When totalStaked == 0 But Rewards Are Collected
In `_harvest`, after calling `IStakeDaoGauge(pool.gauge).claim_rewards(address(this), address(this))`, there is a check `if (pool.totalStaked == 0) return (tokens, amounts)`. This means if rewards are claimed from the gauge but no one is currently staked, the rewards are collected into the contract's balance but never distributed (accRewardPerShare is not updated). These tokens become permanently stuck in the contract with no mechanism to recover them. This can happen if all stakers withdraw before a harvest, or if the last staker withdraws while rewards are still accumulating in the gauge.


