No Token Recovery Mechanism for Stuck Funds
The BoostHub contract has no function to recover ERC20 tokens that become stuck in the contract. Tokens can become stuck in several scenarios: (1) reward tokens collected when `totalStaked == 0` (as described in a separate finding), (2) precision dust from integer division in reward accounting, (3) tokens accidentally sent to the contract, (4) reward tokens from a pool that is shut down before all rewards are claimed. Once stuck, these tokens are permanently inaccessible.


