BoostHub.sol
Infinite Approval to Gauge Not Revoked on Pool Shutdown
When a pool is added via `addPool`, the contract grants infinite approval (`type(uint256).max`) to the gauge for the pool's asset token: `IERC20(asset).forceApprove(gauge, type(uint256).max)`. When a pool is shut down via `shutdownPool`, this approval is never revoked. If the gauge contract is later compromised or has a vulnerability, it could still pull tokens from BoostHub even after the pool is shut down. Additionally, if the same asset is used in multiple pools with different gauges, each gauge has infinite approval.


