BoostHub.sol
Reward Accounting Bug in _checkpoint: rewardDebt Updated Using position.principal Instead of Cached principal
In the `_checkpoint` function, the reward debt is updated at the end of the loop using `position.principal` (the live storage value) instead of the cached `principal` variable that was read at the start of the function. While in `_checkpoint` itself this doesn't cause an issue (since principal hasn't changed yet), the pattern is fragile and inconsistent. More critically, the `accumulated` value is computed using the cached `principal`, but `rewardDebt` is set using `position.principal`. If `position.principal` were to change mid-loop (e.g., through a reentrancy or if the function were refactored), this would cause incorrect reward debt calculations. Additionally, the double computation of `position.principal * accRewardPerShare[pid][token] / ACC_PRECISION` (once for `accumulated` using cached `principal`, once for `rewardDebt` using `position.principal`) is redundant and wastes gas.


