BoostHub.sol
Unchecked Withdrawal Amount Against Position Principal Allows Underflow Revert DoS
In the `withdraw` function, `position.principal -= amount` will revert with an underflow if `amount > position.principal`. While Solidity 0.8.x protects against silent underflows, the revert itself is not a custom error and provides no meaningful error message. More importantly, there is no explicit check that `amount <= position.principal` before the subtraction, meaning the error message is a generic arithmetic revert rather than a descriptive custom error. This is a code quality issue that makes debugging harder.


