BoostHub.sol
Precision Loss in Reward Accounting Can Lead to Dust Accumulation
The reward accounting formula `accRewardPerShare[pid][tokens[i]] += net * ACC_PRECISION / pool.totalStaked` uses integer division. When `net * ACC_PRECISION` is not perfectly divisible by `pool.totalStaked`, the remainder is lost. Over many harvest cycles, this dust accumulates in the contract. Similarly, when computing `accumulated = principal * accRewardPerShare[pid][token] / ACC_PRECISION`, precision is lost again. The total claimable by all stakers will always be slightly less than the total harvested (after fees), with the difference stuck in the contract.


