BoostHub.sol
Missing No-Harvest Path in _hasClaimableRewards Can Cause Stale Reward Accounting
The `_hasClaimableRewards` function checks if any reward token has claimable rewards above the minimum threshold. If it returns false, `_harvest` returns early without updating `accRewardPerShare`. However, `_syncGaugeRewards` is called before this check, which can add new reward tokens to the pool. If a new reward token is added but its claimable amount is below the threshold, the token is registered but `accRewardPerShare` for it is never initialized. This is fine since it starts at 0. However, if `_hasClaimableRewards` returns false due to all tokens being below threshold, but some tokens have non-zero claimable amounts, those rewards are silently skipped. The minimum harvest amount is applied globally (same threshold for all tokens), which may be inappropriate for tokens with very different decimal counts.


