BoostHub.sol
accRewardPerShare Can Theoretically Overflow for Long-Running Pools with Small Stakes
The `accRewardPerShare` accumulator is updated as: `accRewardPerShare[pid][tokens[i]] += net * ACC_PRECISION / pool.totalStaked`. For a pool with very small `totalStaked` (e.g., 1 wei) and large reward amounts, `net * ACC_PRECISION / pool.totalStaked` could be very large. Over many harvest cycles, `accRewardPerShare` could theoretically overflow `uint256`. While `uint256` is extremely large (2^256 - 1), in extreme edge cases (e.g., 1 wei staked, large rewards, many harvests), this could be a concern. Solidity 0.8.x would revert on overflow, causing a DoS.


