BoostHub.sol
Approved Strategy Can Be Revoked While Having Active Position - Withdrawal Still Allowed But Deposit Blocked
When an owner revokes a strategy's approval via `approveStrategy(strategy, pid, false)`, the strategy can no longer deposit but can still withdraw (because the withdraw check is `if (!approvedStrategy[pid][msg.sender] && position.principal == 0)`). However, the strategy cannot call `harvest` (which requires `whenNotPaused` but not approval) or `claim` (which uses `_canClaim` that allows claiming if principal > 0 or claimable > 0). This creates an inconsistent state where a de-approved strategy is in a limbo: it can withdraw and claim but cannot deposit. The issue is that there's no way for the strategy to harvest rewards for itself after being de-approved, since `harvest` is a pool-level operation that benefits all stakers.
